    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>Digital Literacy Course for Seniors</h1>
            <p>Welcome to the digital literacy course! This program will guide you through essential skills to confidently navigate the digital world.</p>
        </header>

        <!-- Module 1 -->
        <div class="module">
            <h2>Module 1: Online Banking - Secure and Simple</h2>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Learn to manage personal finances securely and efficiently.</p>
            <p><strong>Objectives:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Create and log into an online banking account.</li>
                <li>Perform basic tasks: check balances, pay bills, and transfer funds securely.</li>
                <li>Recognize secure banking practices.</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="scenario">
                <strong>Practical Scenario:</strong>
                <p>Simulate paying a utility bill using a mock online banking interface. Follow the on-screen prompts to complete the payment process securely.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Module 2 -->
        <div class="module">
            <h2>Module 2: Video Calling - Stay Connected</h2>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Connect with family, friends, and professionals through video calls.</p>
            <p><strong>Objectives:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Install and create accounts on platforms like Zoom or Skype.</li>
                <li>Understand features like muting, screen sharing, and camera settings.</li>
                <li>Join and host virtual meetings.</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="scenario">
                <strong>Practical Scenario:</strong>
                <p>Join a simulated family video call. Practice adjusting microphone settings and sharing your screen during the session.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Module 3 -->
        <div class="module">
            <h2>Module 3: Social Media Use - Stay Engaged</h2>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Safely and effectively engage with social media platforms.</p>
            <p><strong>Objectives:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Create and set up a social media account (e.g., Facebook).</li>
                <li>Adjust privacy settings to protect personal information.</li>
                <li>Interact with posts, comments, and messages.</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="scenario">
                <strong>Practical Scenario:</strong>
                <p>Create a sample profile and post your first message. Practice adjusting privacy settings to control who can see your content.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Module 4 -->
        <div class="module">
            <h2>Module 4: Cybersecurity Basics - Stay Safe Online</h2>
            <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Identify online threats and adopt secure practices.</p>
            <p><strong>Objectives:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Recognize phishing attempts and avoid scams.</li>
                <li>Create and manage strong passwords.</li>
                <li>Identify secure websites and enable two-factor authentication (2FA).</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="scenario">
                <strong>Practical Scenario:</strong>
                <p>Analyze example phishing emails to identify red flags. Practice setting up 2FA on a mock website.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

